WEBVTT

00:02.213 --> 00:04.215
Meredith:
WHEN EXPOSED TO TRAUMA,

00:04.215 --> 00:06.427
THE BODY DEPLOYS
ITS OWN DEFENSE SYSTEM.

00:06.427 --> 00:07.628
DO YOU KNOW WHY
I RESENT YOU?

00:07.628 --> 00:09.800
I GAVE UP EVERYTHING
FOR YOU.

00:12.893 --> 00:16.187
FROM THE FIRST SECOND
THE BRAIN RECEIVES THE SIGNAL

00:16.187 --> 00:18.899
THAT A CATASTROPHE
HAS HAPPENED...

00:29.570 --> 00:30.781
[ SIGHS ]

00:32.203 --> 00:33.244
YOU HAVE
A PIECE OF PAPER?

00:33.244 --> 00:34.415
FOR WHAT?

00:34.415 --> 00:35.916
WE NEED TO MAKE VOWS.

00:35.916 --> 00:38.289
I-I HAVE POST-ITS.

00:38.289 --> 00:40.161
WHAT DO WE WANT
TO PROMISE EACH OTHER?

00:47.428 --> 00:49.170
...THE BLOOD RUSHES
TO THE ORGANS

00:49.170 --> 00:50.471
THAT NEED HELP THE MOST.

00:52.133 --> 00:54.595
BLOOD FLOODS INTO THE MUSCLES,

00:54.595 --> 00:57.017
THE LUNGS, THE HEART,
THE BRAIN.

00:57.017 --> 00:58.679
[ BEEPING ]

01:10.151 --> 01:14.074
THE BRAIN MAKES A DECISION
FOR THE REST OF THE BODY...

01:20.000 --> 01:22.703
...EITHER FACE THE DANGER
OR RUN AWAY.

01:31.342 --> 01:34.515
IT'S A MECHANISM DESIGNED TO
PROTECT THE BODY FROM HARM...

01:36.217 --> 01:38.979
[ CRICKETS CHIRPING ]

01:56.116 --> 01:57.328
[ SIGHS ]

01:59.039 --> 02:01.162
...FROM KNOWING
THAT WHAT HAS HAPPENED

02:01.162 --> 02:02.703
MIGHT BE IRREPARABLE.

02:02.703 --> 02:06.247
TO LOVE EACH OTHER
EVEN WHEN WE HATE EACH OTHER.

02:06.247 --> 02:07.628
NO RUNNING.

02:11.962 --> 02:13.093
WE CALL IT...

02:14.515 --> 02:15.846
...SHOCK.

02:25.186 --> 02:26.767
Lynn: THE PERSON
WHO CARES FOR YOUR KIDS

02:26.767 --> 02:28.028
IS AN IMPORTANT CHOICE.

02:28.028 --> 02:29.650
YOU WANT TO MAKE SURE
IT'S THE RIGHT FIT.

02:29.650 --> 02:31.151
SO WE'LL SIT AND TALK.

02:31.151 --> 02:33.274
I'LL FIND OUT ABOUT YOUR NEEDS,
YOU'LL LEARN ABOUT ME --

02:33.274 --> 02:35.576
RIGHT. JUST, RIGHT NOW,
I'M A LITTLE PRESSED FOR TIME.

02:35.576 --> 02:38.118
OH, ABSOLUTELY. YOU'RE BUSY.
THAT'S WHY WE'RE HERE TO HELP.

02:38.118 --> 02:40.331
YEAH, THERE'S A TRAUMA
COMING IN, AND I --

02:40.331 --> 02:43.043
OF COURSE. LISTEN, I'VE WORKED
WITH DOCTORS BEFORE, MANY TIMES.

02:43.043 --> 02:44.545
I KNOW THE DRILL.

02:44.545 --> 02:46.917
HOW ABOUT IF I WAIT IN THE LOBBY
UNTIL YOU HAVE SOME TIME?

02:46.917 --> 02:48.168
THAT'S GREAT.
I'LL FIND YOU.

02:48.168 --> 02:50.170
OKAY.

02:50.170 --> 02:51.051
WHO WAS THAT?

02:51.051 --> 02:52.673
UH, NEW NANNY,
HOPEFULLY.

02:52.673 --> 02:54.595
[ GASPS ]
YOU GOT A NANNY?

02:54.595 --> 02:56.257
I HAD TO.
DEREK LEFT.

02:56.257 --> 02:57.848
WHAT?

02:57.848 --> 02:59.179
Owen: WE DON'T HAVE
NUMBERS YET...
MEREDITH?
Shh!

02:59.179 --> 03:02.012
...BUT BE PREPARED
FOR AS MANY AS 20 CASUALTIES,

03:02.012 --> 03:03.434
MANY OF THEM KIDS.

03:03.434 --> 03:04.855
WHAT HAPPENED?
[ DOCTORS MURMUR ]

03:04.855 --> 03:07.147
A WOMAN DROVE OFF A BRIDGE
WITH HER TWO KIDS IN THE CAR.

03:07.147 --> 03:09.980
WITNESSES ARE SAYING
THAT THE WOMAN STARTED SPEEDING,

03:09.980 --> 03:11.482
SHE RAMMED
A BUNCH OF VEHICLES,

03:11.482 --> 03:13.444
AND THEN TOOK A SHARP RIGHT
OFF THE BRIDGE

03:13.444 --> 03:14.985
I-INTO THE WATER.

03:14.985 --> 03:16.657
POLICE BELIEVE
THIS WAS INTENTIONAL.

03:16.657 --> 03:17.658
OH, MY GOD.

03:17.658 --> 03:18.869
WITH HER KIDS?

03:18.869 --> 03:20.080
LET'S COOPERATE
WITH THE POLICE

03:20.080 --> 03:22.493
AND DO OUR JOBS,
OKAY?

03:22.493 --> 03:24.245
GOD, IS SHE
ONE OF THOSE CRAZY MOMS

03:24.245 --> 03:25.876
WHO TRIES
TO DROWN HER KIDS?

03:25.876 --> 03:27.037
[ SIGHS ]

03:27.037 --> 03:29.460
MAYBE SHE NEEDED A NANNY.

03:29.460 --> 03:31.542
WHAT KIND OF MOTHER
DOES THAT TO HER OWN KIDS?

03:31.542 --> 03:33.884
WHY IS IT SOMEHOW WORSE
WHEN A WOMAN KILLS HER KIDS?

03:33.884 --> 03:35.095
THAT'S SEXIST.

03:35.095 --> 03:38.218
WOMEN ARE JUST AS CRAPPY
AND HOMICIDAL AS MEN.

03:38.218 --> 03:40.050
IS THERE SOMETHING
YOU WANT TO TELL ME?

03:40.050 --> 03:41.051
OR A GRAND JURY?

03:41.051 --> 03:42.933
SHUT UP.
I'M JUST MAKING A POINT.

03:42.933 --> 03:45.185
IT'S NOT LIKE I'M ADVOCATING
KILLING YOUR KIDS.

03:45.185 --> 03:46.517
OH, HI, DR. KEPNER.

03:46.517 --> 03:48.188
YOU HEARD DR. HUNT.
WE'VE GOT AT LEAST
SIX CRITICALS ON THE WAY.

03:48.188 --> 03:49.189
WHY ARE YOU BOTH
STANDING THERE?

03:49.189 --> 03:50.190
YOU'RE RIGHT.
I'M SORRY.

03:50.190 --> 03:52.192
[ SIGHS ]

03:52.192 --> 03:53.944
I TOLD JACKSON
ABOUT THE BABY.

03:53.944 --> 03:55.356
OH, GOD.

03:55.356 --> 03:57.278
I WAS JUST STANDING HERE
SHOUTING ABOUT KILLING KIDS.

03:57.278 --> 03:58.659
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL ME
TO SHUT UP?

03:58.659 --> 03:59.660
DOES SHE KNOW?

03:59.660 --> 04:01.121
UH, I DON'T KNOW.

04:01.121 --> 04:02.242
NO. RIGHT?

04:02.242 --> 04:04.164
I MEAN, IF SHE KNEW --

04:04.164 --> 04:07.788
IF YOU FOUND OUT
THAT YOUR UNBORN BABY
HAD A FATAL DISEASE,

04:07.788 --> 04:09.370
YOU WOULDN'T BE AT WORK,
RIGHT?

04:09.370 --> 04:10.791
NO.

04:10.791 --> 04:13.003
[ SIREN WAILING ]

04:13.003 --> 04:14.174
WHAT DO WE GOT?

04:14.174 --> 04:15.876
10-YEAR-OLD FEMALE,
MIA JAMES.

04:15.876 --> 04:17.928
GCS OF 14 BUT WAS UNCONSCIOUS
AT THE SCENE.

04:17.928 --> 04:19.139
DEEP FACIAL LAC.

04:19.139 --> 04:21.221
LITTLE BROTHER AND MOM
ARE RIGHT BEHIND US.

04:21.221 --> 04:23.183
MIA, I'M DR. HUNT.
CAN YOU HEAR ME?

04:23.183 --> 04:24.725
WHERE'S MY MOM?
IS SHE OKAY?

04:24.725 --> 04:26.807
WE'LL FIND OUT AS SOON
AS WE CAN. LET'S GET HER INSIDE.

04:26.807 --> 04:28.889
PARKER JAMES, AGE 5.

04:28.889 --> 04:30.230
MINOR INJURIES INCLUDE
FACIAL LACERATIONS,

04:30.230 --> 04:31.652
LEFT-ARM DEFORMITY,
NORMAL VITALS.

04:31.652 --> 04:32.773
WHERE'S MY SISTER?

04:32.773 --> 04:34.945
SHE'S RIGHT INSIDE, PARKER.
WE'VE GOT YOU, OKAY?

04:36.026 --> 04:39.029
Paramedic:
WE GOT A BROOKE JAMES,
SUBMERGED RESTRAINED DRIVER,

04:39.029 --> 04:41.362
UNRESPONSIVE SINCE WE ARRIVED
ON THE SCENE.

04:41.362 --> 04:43.243
SHE IS HYPOTENSIVE,
TACHYCARDIC.

04:43.243 --> 04:45.115
WAIT --
IS THIS THE DRIVER?
YEAH.

04:45.115 --> 04:46.827
LET'S MOVE.
COME ON.

04:46.827 --> 04:49.670
[ SIRENS WAILING ]

04:49.670 --> 04:52.373
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

04:52.373 --> 04:53.544
POLICE WANT
TO QUESTION HER,

04:53.544 --> 04:55.045
BUT I SAID THERE'S NO WAY
IN HER CONDITION.

04:55.045 --> 04:56.837
DID THEY SAY WHAT HAPPENED?
DID SHE GO NUTS?

04:56.837 --> 04:59.340
SHE COULD HAVE LOST HER FOOTING
ON THE GAS PEDAL.

04:59.340 --> 05:01.091
WE DO NOT KNOW.

05:01.091 --> 05:03.974
WE DO KNOW SHE'S HYPOTENSIVE,
HAD A LOW D-STICK READING AND...

05:03.974 --> 05:05.426
FREE FLUID IN THE BELLY.

05:05.426 --> 05:07.137
SHE'S TOO UNSTABLE
FOR A C.T.

05:07.137 --> 05:08.889
LET'S GET HER
UP TO THE O.R. NOW.

05:10.100 --> 05:13.564
HUNT. DRIVER'S IN BAD SHAPE.
WE'RE TAKING HER UP.

05:13.564 --> 05:15.105
I'M GONNA ALERT THE O.R.

05:15.105 --> 05:17.197
I-I'M LOOKING
FOR MY WIFE AND KIDS.

05:17.197 --> 05:20.240
UH, UH, BROOKE JAMES.
UH, KIDS ARE MIA AND --

05:20.240 --> 05:21.532
PARKER, RIGHT?

05:21.532 --> 05:23.033
THEY SAID
SOME WOMAN HIT THEIR CAR

05:23.033 --> 05:23.994
AND DROVE OFF THE BRIDGE?

05:23.994 --> 05:25.866
MR. JAMES, YOUR WIFE
IS ON HER WAY TO SURGERY.

05:25.866 --> 05:27.448
YOUR KIDS
ARE BEING TREATED.

05:27.448 --> 05:30.040
YOUR WIFE WAS THE DRIVER.

05:30.040 --> 05:32.623
SHE...
DROVE OFF THE BRIDGE.

05:32.623 --> 05:33.624
WHAT?

05:33.624 --> 05:35.045
OH, NO.
T-THAT'S CRAZY.

05:35.045 --> 05:36.126
SIR --

05:36.126 --> 05:37.628
NO, SHE WOULDN'T DO THAT.
THAT'S CRAZY.

05:37.628 --> 05:39.049
MR. JAMES,
CAN YOU COME WITH US?
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.
EXCUSE ME.

05:39.049 --> 05:40.220
SHE WOULDN'T DO THAT.
CAN YOU COME WITH US?

05:40.220 --> 05:41.341
MR. JAMES --
THANK YOU, SIR.

05:41.341 --> 05:42.553
SHE'D NEVER DO THAT.
IT'S A LIE!

05:42.553 --> 05:44.845
I'M HERE.
WE'RE ON OUR WAY UP.

05:44.845 --> 05:46.136
I'M GONNA WANT MORE SCANS,

05:46.136 --> 05:48.058
3-D RENDERINGS SO I CAN
GET TO KNOW THIS TUMOR BETTER.

05:48.058 --> 05:50.350
I'M GONNA NEED TO DRAW UP
MEASUREMENTS AND TRAJECTORIES.

05:50.350 --> 05:52.232
WHEN DO I GET TO SPEAK
TO HER PREVIOUS DOCTORS?

05:52.232 --> 05:54.395
UM, WELL, AS SOON AS
I TALK TO DR. HERMAN.

05:54.395 --> 05:56.647
GREAT.
WHEN ARE YOU DOING THAT?

05:58.939 --> 06:00.861
IT'S A BIG CLIFF.
YOU JUST GOT TO LEAP.

06:00.861 --> 06:02.072
I STOLE
MEDICAL RECORDS.

06:02.072 --> 06:04.154
I RACKED UP ABOUT
A THOUSAND HIPAA VIOLATIONS.

06:04.154 --> 06:05.616
IT'S NOT A CLIFF.
THAT'S PRISON.

06:05.616 --> 06:07.197
AND I'M TOO PRETTY
FOR PRISON.

06:07.197 --> 06:09.540
ARIZONA,
YOU ARE SAVING HER LIFE.

06:09.540 --> 06:12.413
WELL, I'M SAVING HER LIFE,
BUT YOU MADE IT POSSIBLE.

06:12.413 --> 06:14.755
ONCE YOU TELL HER,
ONCE SHE UNDERSTANDS,

06:14.755 --> 06:16.627
SHE -- SHE WILL
BE OKAY WITH IT.

06:16.627 --> 06:17.998
SHE'LL BE HAPPY.

06:17.998 --> 06:19.880
ULTIMATELY,
SHE WILL BE THRILLED.

06:21.381 --> 06:22.843
YOU WANT ME
TO TELL HER?

06:22.843 --> 06:24.715
NO. I HAVE TO DO IT.
I HAVE TO DO IT.

06:24.715 --> 06:26.677
I JUST NEED TO FIGURE OUT
HOW AND WHEN.

06:26.677 --> 06:28.388
HOW AND WHEN.

06:31.932 --> 06:34.014
THAT'S MY TUMOR.

06:34.014 --> 06:35.976
THAT'S MY TUMOR!

06:35.976 --> 06:39.690
WHERE DID YOU GET IT
AND WHY DO YOU HAVE IT?!

06:46.156 --> 06:49.329
YOU SHOWED MY TUMOR
TO OTHER DOCTORS,

06:49.329 --> 06:50.330
WITHOUT MY CONSENT --

06:50.330 --> 06:51.371
I NEEDED TO UNDERSTAND --

06:51.371 --> 06:52.953
YOU HAVE NO RIGHT.
YOU STOLE THEM.

06:52.953 --> 06:54.164
I HAD TO.

06:54.164 --> 06:56.747
DO YOU KNOW HOW MANY LAWS
YOU'RE BREAKING RIGHT NOW?

06:56.747 --> 06:58.208
YOU WEREN'T TELLING ME
ANYTHING!

06:58.208 --> 06:59.209
I CAN REMOVE THE TUMOR.

06:59.209 --> 07:01.592
I DON'T KNOW WHO YOU'VE BEEN
SEEING FOR THIS.

07:01.592 --> 07:02.753
I'M SURE THEY'RE GREAT.

07:02.753 --> 07:04.885
I'M SURE THEY ARE
THE BEST IN THEIR FIELD.

07:04.885 --> 07:08.048
BUT I CAN ONLY TELL YOU,
THEY LACK IMAGINATION.

07:08.048 --> 07:09.219
THEY LACK SCOPE.

07:10.721 --> 07:13.393
YOUR TUMOR IS SMART.

07:13.393 --> 07:14.645
IT'S BRILLIANT.

07:14.645 --> 07:17.688
BUT SO AM I.
I CAN BEAT IT.

07:17.688 --> 07:19.189
I WILL BEAT IT.

07:25.235 --> 07:26.697
I HAVE A SURGERY.

07:28.829 --> 07:32.032
[ DOOR OPENS ]

07:36.206 --> 07:37.788
CHIEF, UH,
JUST WANTED TO LET YOU KNOW

07:37.788 --> 07:39.710
THAT I DON'T THINK
KEPNER'S GONNA MAKE IT IN TODAY.

07:39.710 --> 07:41.131
WE HAD SOME NEWS, UM --

07:41.131 --> 07:42.132
APRIL'S HERE.

07:43.083 --> 07:44.044
WAIT. WHAT?

07:44.044 --> 07:45.636
YEAH. SHE'S BEEN HERE
ALL MORNING.

07:45.636 --> 07:46.927
SHE'S JUST ON HER WAY
UP TO SURGERY.

07:46.927 --> 07:47.928
EVERYTHING OKAY?

07:47.928 --> 07:50.851
UH, YEAH, YEAH.
THANK YOU.

07:50.851 --> 07:51.762
[ SIGHS ]

07:51.762 --> 07:53.143
YOU KNOW WHAT? NO.

07:53.143 --> 07:55.686
ACTUALLY, I NEED YOU TO PULL HER
OUT OF SURGERY RIGHT NOW.

07:55.686 --> 07:56.597
AVERY, I CAN'T --

07:56.597 --> 07:58.058
NO, LOOK.
SHE SHOULDN'T OPERATE.

07:58.058 --> 07:59.980
SHE SHOULDN'T EVEN BE
AT WORK TODAY AT ALL,

07:59.980 --> 08:01.812
SO SHE SHOULD DEFINITELY
NOT BE OPERATING.

08:01.812 --> 08:03.273
I NEED YOU TRUST ME
WHEN I SAY THAT.

08:04.775 --> 08:07.027
April:
KELLY, MORE LAP PADS? I THINK
I SEE THE SOURCE OF THE CUT.

08:07.027 --> 08:08.108
I GOT IT.

08:10.490 --> 08:11.912
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

08:11.912 --> 08:13.113
OWEN?

08:13.113 --> 08:14.875
GREY. KEPNER.
HOW WE DOING IN HERE?

08:14.875 --> 08:16.827
WELL, IT'S A MESS,
BUT WE'VE GOT IT UNDER CONTROL.

08:18.999 --> 08:22.002
APRIL,
I'M...TAGGING YOU OUT.

08:22.002 --> 08:24.044
I'LL TAKE THIS ONE.

08:24.044 --> 08:25.045
WHY?

08:25.045 --> 08:26.887
I'LL JUST --
I'LL TAKE THIS ONE.

08:29.760 --> 08:30.971
APRIL.

08:30.971 --> 08:33.343
I'M GOOD.
YOU CAN GO.

08:33.343 --> 08:35.095
I-IT'S OKAY.
I'M TAGGING YOU OUT.

08:35.095 --> 08:35.806
NO.

08:38.729 --> 08:39.770
OWEN?

08:39.770 --> 08:42.102
LISTEN, IT'S OKAY.
WE'VE GOT THIS.

08:42.102 --> 08:44.064
GO AHEAD AND GO.
[ SCOFFS ]

08:44.064 --> 08:45.145
DO WE HAVE
A PROBLEM HERE?

08:45.145 --> 08:46.066
NO --

08:46.066 --> 08:48.068
YES. YES, THERE IS --
JACKSON.

08:48.068 --> 08:49.740
JACKSON'S MY PROBLEM,
RIGHT, HUNT?

08:49.740 --> 08:51.491
HE WENT TO YOU,
AND NOW YOU KNOW,

08:51.491 --> 08:53.323
AND YOU'VE DECIDED
WHAT'S BEST FOR ME.

08:53.323 --> 08:56.206
JACKSON'S DOWNSTAIRS,
AND HE'S WAITING FOR YOU.

08:56.206 --> 08:57.658
WELL, I'M WORKING HERE.

09:00.210 --> 09:02.753
APRIL...

09:02.753 --> 09:04.124
I AM TAKING OVER FOR YOU.

09:04.124 --> 09:06.216
[ SCOFFS ] IS THIS AN ORDER?
IS THAT WHAT'S HAPPENING?

09:06.216 --> 09:07.758
ARE YOU ORDERING ME
OUT OF MY O.R.?

09:07.758 --> 09:09.720
[ SIGHS ]

09:09.720 --> 09:10.841
I'M ASKING YOU.

09:10.841 --> 09:12.052
WELL, THEN,
MY ANSWER IS NO.

09:13.343 --> 09:14.675
THEN IT IS AN ORDER.

09:14.675 --> 09:16.266
[ SCOFFS ]

09:16.266 --> 09:19.059
THAT IS AN ORDER,
KEPNER.

09:19.059 --> 09:20.060
FINE.

09:29.029 --> 09:31.191
YOU'RE IN
SO MUCH TROUBLE.

09:31.191 --> 09:33.824
SHUT UP. YOU ARE.
YOU WANTED TO GO OUT.

09:33.824 --> 09:36.617
Bailey:
GOT SOME BRUISES AND CONTUSIONS,
NOTHING SURGICAL.

09:36.617 --> 09:38.749
YOU GUYS HAD
A PRETTY ROUGH RIDE, HUH?

09:38.749 --> 09:40.040
IT WAS AWESOME.

09:40.040 --> 09:41.411
THAT CAR
SLAMMED RIGHT INTO US.

09:41.411 --> 09:45.085
AND THEN THEY FLEW OFF
THE BRIDGE, INTO THE WATER!

09:45.085 --> 09:46.126
AND THEN
ALL THE OTHER CARS

09:46.126 --> 09:48.258
STARTED SLAMMING INTO
EACH OTHER!

09:48.258 --> 09:50.420
IT WAS LIKE
"GRAND THEFT AUTO"!

09:50.420 --> 09:52.472
SON OF A BITCH. DAD'S GONNA
FREAK WHEN HE SEES THE CAR.

09:52.472 --> 09:53.804
LANGUAGE.

09:53.804 --> 09:55.555
WHERE IS YOUR DAD?
YOU CAN'T TELL MY DAD.

09:55.555 --> 09:57.848
YEAH, 'CAUSE HE'S GONNA
GROUND YOU TILL YOU'RE DEAD.

09:57.848 --> 09:59.429
SHUT YOUR MOUTH,
ASSFACE!

09:59.429 --> 10:00.981
YOU'RE AN ASSFACE.

10:00.981 --> 10:02.813
YOU WANT TO BE SO COOL,

10:02.813 --> 10:05.936
BUT YOU'RE A CRAPPY DRIVER,
AND YOUR MUSTACHE IS STUPID.

10:05.936 --> 10:07.067
WAIT --
YOU WERE DRIVING?

10:07.067 --> 10:08.188
HOW OLD ARE YOU?

10:08.188 --> 10:09.189
18.

10:09.189 --> 10:11.992
YEAH,
AND I'M 25, ASSFACE.

10:11.992 --> 10:12.943
HEY, SHH, SHH.

10:14.865 --> 10:16.286
DUODENAL PERF --
DUCT LOOKS SEVERED.

10:16.286 --> 10:18.038
HEAD OF THE PANCREAS
IS BADLY INJURED.

10:18.038 --> 10:19.159
WHAT DO YOU THINK --
TRAUMA WHIPPLE?

10:19.159 --> 10:20.040
LOOKS LIKE IT.

10:20.040 --> 10:22.542
WHAT HAPPENED
WITH YOU AND KEPNER?

10:22.542 --> 10:24.004
NOTHING.

10:24.004 --> 10:25.205
WELL, IT BETTER
HAVE BEEN SOMETHING.

10:25.205 --> 10:26.626
YOU KICKED HER OUT
OF HER OWN O.R.

10:26.626 --> 10:28.338
SHE SHOULDN'T EVEN BE
IN AN O.R.

10:28.338 --> 10:30.170
SHE'S GOT...
PERSONAL STUFF.

10:30.170 --> 10:33.093
WE ALL HAVE PERSONAL STUFF.
MY HUSBAND LEFT ME. I'M HERE.

10:33.093 --> 10:34.174
WAIT. WHAT?

10:36.016 --> 10:37.718
I THOUGHT HE WOULD HAVE
E-MAILED YOU BY NOW.

10:37.718 --> 10:38.759
HE WENT TO D.C.

10:38.759 --> 10:39.890
WHEN DID THIS HAPPEN?

10:39.890 --> 10:40.891
LAST NIGHT.

10:40.891 --> 10:42.182
YOU WANT TO THROW ME OUT?

10:42.182 --> 10:44.975
SHOULD I GO GET MY NAILS DONE,
HAVE A GOOD CRY?

10:44.975 --> 10:46.436
[ SCOFFS ] LISTEN, JACKSON
DIDN'T TELL ME WHAT IT WAS,

10:46.436 --> 10:47.607
JUST THAT --

10:47.607 --> 10:49.229
OH, SO HER HUSBAND TELLS YOU
TO DO SOMETHING,

10:49.229 --> 10:51.151
AND THAT'S ENOUGH --
OKAY,
IT'S ABOUT THEIR BABY.

10:52.652 --> 10:53.653
IT'S BAD.

10:59.449 --> 11:01.992
[ DISTORTED CONVERSATIONS,
MONITORS BEEPING ]

11:15.345 --> 11:18.508
[ BEEPING, THUMP ]

11:21.972 --> 11:23.603
[ WHEELS ROLLING ]

11:23.603 --> 11:25.515
[ DISTORTION STOPS ]

11:25.515 --> 11:27.357
[ SIRENS WAILING ]

11:27.357 --> 11:29.900
Police officer: AND THEN
YOUR MOM STARTED DRIVING FASTER.

11:29.900 --> 11:32.112
DID SHE SAY ANYTHING?

11:32.112 --> 11:34.364
SHE -- SHE TOLD US
TO SHUT UP.

11:34.364 --> 11:35.445
SHE SAID THAT?

11:35.445 --> 11:37.117
SHE'S NEVER SAID THAT.

11:37.117 --> 11:39.910
[ Voice breaking ]
WE WEREN'T EVEN MAKING NOISE.

11:39.910 --> 11:42.282
AND THEN WE STARTED
TO HIT OTHER CARS,

11:42.282 --> 11:44.534
AND THEN
WE WENT INTO THE WATER,

11:44.534 --> 11:46.416
AND THEN
A FIREMAN PULLED ME OUT.

11:46.416 --> 11:48.128
OH, GOD.

11:48.128 --> 11:51.001
YOU SAID
"SHUT UP" WAS A BAD WORD.

11:51.001 --> 11:52.883
YOU SAID --

11:52.883 --> 11:55.425
NO, IT'S OKAY.
YOU'RE OKAY.

11:55.425 --> 11:58.098
IT'S TRUE, PARKER.
YOU'RE A LUCKY KID.

11:58.098 --> 12:00.100
ALL YOU NEED IS A LITTLE SPLINT
ON THAT WRIST,

12:00.100 --> 12:01.221
BUT THAT'S IT.

12:01.221 --> 12:02.893
Jackson: OKAY.

12:02.893 --> 12:05.145
WELL, YOUR DAUGHTER'S STILL
JUST A LITTLE GROGGY.

12:05.145 --> 12:07.187
JUST NEED TO STITCH UP
THAT LACERATION ON HER FACE.

12:07.187 --> 12:08.849
SHE'S GOOD TO GO.
Greg: YES. OF COURSE.

12:08.849 --> 12:10.480
PLEASE, DO WHATEVER
YOU HAVE TO DO.

12:10.480 --> 12:11.982
DR. AVERY, A WORD?

12:11.982 --> 12:13.984
UH...EXCUSE ME.

12:13.984 --> 12:15.485
ONE SECOND.

12:20.200 --> 12:21.451
HEY. YOU ALL RIGHT?

12:21.451 --> 12:23.123
I'LL GET SOMEBODY TO
COVER FOR ME, AND WE
CAN JUST GO HOME --

12:23.123 --> 12:24.744
WHAT IS WRONG WITH YOU?

12:24.744 --> 12:26.286
LETTING A COP
INTERROGATE A 5-YEAR-OLD?

12:26.286 --> 12:28.208
THEY...NEEDED TO KNOW --

12:28.208 --> 12:30.871
THOSE TWO KIDS WERE
ALMOST KILLED BY THEIR MOTHER.

12:30.871 --> 12:32.212
T-THEY ARE --
THEY'RE TERRIFIED.

12:32.212 --> 12:33.583
OKAY. SLOW DOWN.
THEY'RE --
THEY'RE IN SHOCK.

12:33.583 --> 12:35.505
LISTEN, LISTEN, I THINK
YOU'RE IN SHOCK, ACTUALLY.

12:35.505 --> 12:37.547
THEY SHOULDN'T EVEN BE
DOWN HERE. GET THEM OUT OF HERE.

12:37.547 --> 12:39.089
GET THEM SOMEPLACE SAFE.
GET THEM ADMITTED.

12:39.089 --> 12:40.760
OKAY.
LET'S JUST GO HOME.

12:40.760 --> 12:43.143
HAVE YOU SEEN
THOSE PEOPLE IN THERE?!

12:43.143 --> 12:44.304
WHAT THAT WOMAN DID?!

12:44.304 --> 12:45.936
I KNOW, AND THERE ARE
PLENTY OF PEOPLE HERE

12:45.936 --> 12:47.227
THAT CAN TAKE CARE OF THEM,
RIGHT?

12:47.227 --> 12:48.228
YOU NEED TO --

12:48.228 --> 12:51.311
I -- I NEED TO BE
IN AN O.R.

12:51.311 --> 12:53.894
BUT YOU SEEM TO BE MAKING ALL
SORTS OF DECISIONS FOR ME TODAY.

12:53.894 --> 12:55.105
I'M TRYING TO HELP YOU.

12:55.105 --> 12:56.276
YEAH, WELL,
YOU'RE NOT HELPING.

12:56.276 --> 12:58.068
YOU GO TO OWEN,
AND THEN TWO MEN DECIDE

12:58.068 --> 12:59.779
WHAT THEY THINK IS BEST
FOR THE LITTLE LADY,

12:59.779 --> 13:01.201
LIKE I'M
SOME HELPLESS IDIOT,

13:01.201 --> 13:03.743
AND THEN I SUDDENLY FIND MYSELF
STANDING OUTSIDE OF MY O.R.?

13:03.743 --> 13:05.866
THAT -- THAT --
THAT IS NOT HELPING!

13:05.866 --> 13:07.037
WHY DON'T YOU TELL ME
WHAT IS, THEN?

13:07.037 --> 13:08.909
TALK TO ME
INSTEAD OF RUNNING AWAY.

13:08.909 --> 13:11.912
TELL ME WHAT YOU NEED.
TELL ME WHAT I CAN DO.
TELL ME HOW YOU FEEL.

13:11.912 --> 13:15.005
TELL ME SOMETHING -- ANYTHING.
SAY SOMETHING. TALK TO ME.

13:15.005 --> 13:16.837
I'M TRYING TO HELP YOU. THAT'S
ALL I'M TRYING TO DO HERE.

13:16.837 --> 13:18.008
OKAY, OKAY.

13:18.008 --> 13:19.259
YOU WANT TO HELP?
YES.

13:19.259 --> 13:20.720
JUST GET THAT FAMILY
INTO A ROOM

13:20.720 --> 13:23.423
AND STITCH UP
THAT GIRL'S FACE.

13:34.144 --> 13:36.436
[ SIGHS ]

13:36.436 --> 13:38.778
[ BREATHING DEEPLY ]

13:45.205 --> 13:46.116
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

13:46.116 --> 13:47.908
EVERYTHING OKAY?

13:50.210 --> 13:52.042
[ LAUGHING ]

14:04.594 --> 14:06.176
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

14:11.771 --> 14:13.523
NO.

14:16.736 --> 14:19.359
EVERYTHING IS NOT OKAY.

14:25.745 --> 14:27.697
Bailey:
WE NEED YOUR PARENTS' NAMES.

14:27.697 --> 14:30.080
THEY NEED TO KNOW THAT
YOU'RE HERE AND YOU'RE SAFE.

14:30.080 --> 14:31.201
JUST COUGH IT UP.

14:31.201 --> 14:33.253
YOU DON'T SAY
A WORD.

14:33.253 --> 14:34.834
YOU'RE
A BRICK WALL.

14:34.834 --> 14:36.876
DYLAN'S C.T. SHOWS
MESENTERIC STRANDING

14:36.876 --> 14:38.588
AND SOME THICKENING
OF THE BOWEL WALL.

14:38.588 --> 14:40.380
COULD BE
JUST A MESENTERIC INJURY,

14:40.380 --> 14:42.302
BUT IT ALSO LOOKS LIKE
A BUCKET-HANDLE INJURY.

14:42.302 --> 14:44.965
I'LL JUST GO IN
AND TAKE A LOOK FIRST
WITH THE LAPAROSCOPE.

14:44.965 --> 14:46.596
NUH-UNH!

14:46.596 --> 14:48.098
NO. COME HERE.

14:51.221 --> 14:52.512
NO, WE NEED
TO GET IN THERE,

14:52.512 --> 14:54.224
OPEN HIM UP,
AND SEE WHAT'S HAPPENING.

14:54.224 --> 14:55.936
LAPAROSCOPIC
ISN'T THE STANDARD.

14:55.936 --> 14:56.977
YOU COULD MISS
A BOWEL PERF --

14:56.977 --> 14:58.318
BUT I'M TRYING
TO SAVE THIS KID

14:58.318 --> 14:59.819
A MASSIVE SCAR
AND A LONG RECOVERY.

14:59.819 --> 15:00.981
YEAH,
BUT WE SHOULDN'T RISK --

15:00.981 --> 15:02.442
WHY DO YOU
KEEP SAYING "WE"?

15:02.442 --> 15:04.154
YOU'RE NOT DOING IT AT ALL.
HE'S A KID.

15:04.154 --> 15:06.116
YOU DON'T TELL ME
WHAT I'M DOING AND NOT DO--

15:06.116 --> 15:07.237
YOU'RE A KID.

15:07.237 --> 15:10.080
I'M AN ATTENDING PEDIATRIC
SURGEON, AND HE'S A KID.

15:10.080 --> 15:12.532
IT'S MY CALL, AND I'M GOING IN
LAPAROSCOPICALLY.

15:12.532 --> 15:14.794
OHHH.

15:14.794 --> 15:16.206
IS THAT
HOW IT'S GONNA BE?

15:16.206 --> 15:17.297
YEAH. IT IS.

15:17.297 --> 15:18.628
AND MAYBE
WHILE I DO THAT,

15:18.628 --> 15:20.170
YOU CAN GET
HIS LITTLE RAT BROTHER

15:20.170 --> 15:21.801
TO ROLL OVER
ON HIS PARENTS.

15:21.801 --> 15:22.802
OKAY?

15:26.096 --> 15:27.387
LET'S GET HIM
READY TO ROLL.

15:27.387 --> 15:28.969
YOU'RE A BRICK WALL,
JACK.

15:28.969 --> 15:29.970
BRICK IT!

15:34.684 --> 15:39.019
OKAY, THAT SHOULD PREVENT
ANY TAMPONADING.

15:39.019 --> 15:42.402
ONE WOMAN LOSES IT, AND LOOK
AT ALL THE DAMAGE SHE CAN DO.

15:42.402 --> 15:44.444
THERE'S A CHEST CONTUSION
WITH INTERMITTENT ARRHYTHMIAS

15:44.444 --> 15:45.485
IN BED 6.

15:45.485 --> 15:46.987
CAN YOU
TAKE A LOOK AT THAT NEXT?

15:46.987 --> 15:48.488
MM-HMM.

15:48.488 --> 15:49.739
BOY OR GIRL?

15:49.739 --> 15:50.570
WHAT?

15:50.570 --> 15:53.453
OH, ARE YOU GUYS
NOT FINDING OUT?

15:53.453 --> 15:54.874
I AM
SUCH A CONTROL FREAK.

15:54.874 --> 15:57.207
I DON'T THINK
I COULD HANDLE NOT KNOWING.

15:57.207 --> 16:00.000
I WOULD WANT TO HAVE
A LIST OF NAMES IN MIND.

16:00.000 --> 16:02.212
THAT WOULD BE
THE HARDEST PART, I THINK --

16:02.212 --> 16:03.923
CHOOSING THE NAME.

16:03.923 --> 16:07.297
BED 6, CONSULT --
NOW, PLEASE.

16:07.297 --> 16:08.758
OKAY.

16:08.758 --> 16:11.681
UH, I'M LOOKING FOR GREG JAMES.
IS HE STILL DOWN HERE?

16:11.681 --> 16:13.643
I NEED TO TALK TO YOU.

16:13.643 --> 16:16.226
OKAY.
SO, YOU TALKED TO JACKSON.

16:16.226 --> 16:18.228
ARE YOU -- ARE YOU OKAY?
CAN I DO ANYTHING?

16:18.228 --> 16:21.101
YOU SAW SOMETHING
ON MY ULTRASOUND.

16:21.101 --> 16:22.362
YES.

16:22.362 --> 16:25.655
YES, YOU SAW SOMETHING,
AND YOU DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING.

16:25.655 --> 16:27.107
I-I KNOW.
I WASN'T --

16:27.107 --> 16:29.199
I WAS RIGHT THERE
IN THE ROOM.

16:29.199 --> 16:32.372
IT WAS MY BABY,
AND YOU SAID NOTHING.

16:32.372 --> 16:33.493
NOTHING.

16:33.493 --> 16:35.955
I JUST WANTED TO BE SURE
BEFORE I TOLD YOU.

16:35.955 --> 16:38.118
OH, BUT YOU HAD NO PROBLEM
GOING AND TELLING OTHER PEOPLE.

16:38.118 --> 16:40.710
YOU HAD NO PROBLEM
TELLING JACKSON

16:40.710 --> 16:43.333
BEFORE I EVEN HAD
A CHANCE TO PROCESS.

16:43.333 --> 16:44.584
I'M SORRY.

16:44.584 --> 16:47.507
TO HAVE YOU, OF ALL PEOPLE,
KNOWING BEFORE I DID --

16:50.840 --> 16:51.891
I'M SORRY.

16:51.891 --> 16:54.184
YEAH, WELL,
YOU SHOULD BE.

16:54.184 --> 16:55.265
[ SIGHS ]

16:58.017 --> 17:00.980
MR. JAMES IS UPSTAIRS.
HIS KIDS WERE ADMITTED.

17:02.402 --> 17:03.903
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

17:05.195 --> 17:06.646
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

17:06.646 --> 17:08.068
Nurse:
HELLO. THIS IS O.R. 1.

17:08.068 --> 17:10.650
Owen: DID HE TELL AMELIA?
DID HE PASS OFF HIS CASES?

17:10.650 --> 17:11.781
WELL,
I'M SURE HE DID.

17:11.781 --> 17:13.703
DEREK WOULDN'T
JUST LEAVE HIS PATIENTS.

17:13.703 --> 17:14.994
PICKUPS.

17:14.994 --> 17:17.747
[ SIGHS ]
OR HIS WIFE OR HIS KIDS.

17:17.747 --> 17:20.210
I MEAN, IT'S --
IT'S JUST HARD TO BELIEVE.

17:20.210 --> 17:21.081
WELL, HE DID.

17:21.081 --> 17:24.003
AND WHAT DO YOU NEED --
SOMEONE TO BLAME?

17:24.003 --> 17:27.927
IT'S MY FAULT. I DID IT.
I TOLD HIM TO GO.

17:27.927 --> 17:29.089
STAPLER.

17:29.089 --> 17:30.630
DR. GREY,
HER TOX SCREEN'S BACK.

17:30.630 --> 17:33.843
ANY DRUGS OR ALCOHOL?
ANTIPSYCHOTICS? ANTIDEPRESSANTS?

17:33.843 --> 17:34.724
ALL NEGATIVE.

17:34.724 --> 17:35.975
DAMN IT!

17:35.975 --> 17:37.056
WHAT ARE YOU AFTER?

17:37.056 --> 17:38.598
AN EXPLANATION --
SOMETHING.

17:38.598 --> 17:40.560
SOMEONE PUTS HER WHOLE FAMILY
IN DANGER,

17:40.560 --> 17:42.732
YOU WANT TO FIND OUT
THERE WAS A GOOD REASON.

17:44.104 --> 17:47.317
YOU WANT TO BELIEVE
SHE DIDN'T HAVE ANY CHOICE.

17:51.030 --> 17:52.192
HAVE YOU TALKED
TO CRISTINA?

17:52.192 --> 17:55.495
I PRESUME YOU GUYS TALK
ALL THE TIME, ESPECIALLY NOW.

17:55.495 --> 17:58.698
YEAH, WE USUALLY GET ON
THE PHONE FRIDAY NIGHTS FOR ME,

17:58.698 --> 18:01.701
SATURDAY MORNINGS FOR HER,
POUR DRINKS, SETTLE IN.

18:01.701 --> 18:04.043
SO, TODAY'S FRIDAY.
YOU GONNA CALL HER TODAY?

18:04.043 --> 18:08.298
YEAH, I'VE MISSED
THE...LAST COUPLE.

18:08.298 --> 18:09.799
WHY?

18:09.799 --> 18:11.010
WELL, BEFORE SHE LEFT,

18:11.010 --> 18:13.173
SHE SAID SOMETHING
ABOUT DEREK AND I,

18:13.173 --> 18:16.306
AND...SHE WAS RIGHT.

18:16.306 --> 18:19.809
AND I DON'T WANT HER
TO BE RIGHT.

18:21.020 --> 18:23.022
HMM.

18:23.022 --> 18:26.776
Stephanie: OKAY, SO, NO HISTORY
OF DIABETES IN THE FAMILY.

18:26.776 --> 18:30.280
WHAT ABOUT, UH, CURRENT
ILLNESSES OR MENTAL ILLNESSES?

18:30.280 --> 18:32.071
ARE YOU ASKING
IF MY WIFE'S CRAZY?

18:32.071 --> 18:34.364
NO, I'M -- I'M -- WE'RE TRYING
TO SEE IF THERE'S SOMETHING

18:34.364 --> 18:35.865
THAT COULD HAVE
MADE HER DO --

18:35.865 --> 18:38.578
TO HURT MY KIDS?
NOTHING. SHE WOULDN'T.

18:42.292 --> 18:43.953
I DIDN'T THINK SHE WOULD.

18:46.246 --> 18:49.209
BROOKE...
I MEAN, SHE'S, UH...

18:49.209 --> 18:52.131
SHE'S BUSY.

18:52.131 --> 18:55.965
YOU KNOW,
SHE'S TIRED AND STRESSED.

18:55.965 --> 18:57.597
AND SHE FORGETS THINGS.

18:59.058 --> 19:01.060
SHE'S GOT
A LOT GOING ON

19:01.060 --> 19:04.143
WITH GETTING THEM
FROM SCHOOL

19:04.143 --> 19:07.977
AND VIOLIN
AND BASEBALL...

19:07.977 --> 19:09.859
AND MAKING SURE
THEY'RE HAPPY.

19:11.191 --> 19:13.483
AND I...

19:13.483 --> 19:14.984
I WORK TOO MUCH.

19:14.984 --> 19:16.986
I DON'T KNOW.

19:16.986 --> 19:19.489
I...

19:19.489 --> 19:22.161
[ Voice breaking ]
I DON'T KNOW MY WIFE.

19:26.085 --> 19:28.288
I DON'T KNOW ANYTHING
ANYMORE.

19:32.922 --> 19:34.554
I LEFT YOU ALONE
FOR A FEW MINUTES.

19:34.554 --> 19:36.466
AM I GONNA FIND MY WALLET
IN YOUR POCKET?

19:36.466 --> 19:38.758
I'M SORRY THAT I WENT
BEHIND YOUR BACK.

19:38.758 --> 19:41.140
YOU'RE UNDERSTATING IT.
YOU BETRAYED ME.

19:41.140 --> 19:42.262
I THOUGHT
I COULD TRUST YOU.

19:42.262 --> 19:43.563
SHEPHERD IS
FULLY CONVINCED

19:43.563 --> 19:45.014
THAT SHE CAN DO
A COMPLETE RESECTION.

19:45.014 --> 19:46.015
SHE'S CONVINCED --

19:46.015 --> 19:48.187
SHEPHERD IS
IN A PARTY OF ONE.

19:48.187 --> 19:50.109
IF THERE'S EVEN
THE SLIGHTEST BIT OF HOPE,

19:50.109 --> 19:51.811
DON'T YOU WANT
TO KNOW THAT?

19:51.811 --> 19:53.983
ROBBINS, CAN YOU NAME
THE SINGLE WORST,

19:53.983 --> 19:56.776
MOST MALIGNANT SYMPTOM
OF TERMINAL CANCER?

19:56.776 --> 19:58.077
IT'S HOPE.

19:58.077 --> 20:00.870
IT'S RECURRENT,
AND IT KEEPS CREEPING BACK IN,

20:00.870 --> 20:03.323
NO MATTER HOW MANY TIMES
IT GETS RIPPED APART.

20:03.323 --> 20:06.125
MAYO GAVE ME HOPE
IN A PHASE 3 CLINICAL TRIAL.

20:06.125 --> 20:07.247
IT FAILED.

20:07.247 --> 20:10.590
N.Y.U. HOPED
THAT RADIOSURGERY WOULD WORK.

20:10.590 --> 20:11.541
IT DIDN'T.

20:11.541 --> 20:13.673
AND BARROW HAD
HIGH, HIGH HOPES

20:13.673 --> 20:16.296
FOR A POTENT COMBINATION
OF CHEMO AND ABLATION.

20:16.296 --> 20:17.757
NO GO.

20:17.757 --> 20:21.261
AND EVERY TIME THE HOPE GOES,
IT TAKES CHUNKS OF YOU WITH IT,

20:21.261 --> 20:22.932
UNTIL YOU CAN
ONLY FIND COMFORT

20:22.932 --> 20:26.105
IN THE ONE THING THAT YOU KNOW
YOU CAN COUNT ON --

20:26.105 --> 20:28.227
THAT THIS THING
IS GONNA KILL YOU.

20:30.270 --> 20:32.442
SO YOU TELL SHEPHERD
TO KEEP HER HOPE TO HERSELF.

20:32.442 --> 20:35.985
BETTER YET,
TELL HER WHERE TO STICK IT.

20:44.163 --> 20:45.745
OKAY. LET'S START
THE ANASTOMOSES.

20:45.745 --> 20:46.996
YEP.
4-0 PROLENE.

20:46.996 --> 20:48.868
HUSBAND SAYS
THERE'S NO HISTORY OF DIABETES.

20:48.868 --> 20:49.919
ANYTHING ELSE?

20:49.919 --> 20:51.170
UH, YEAH.

20:51.170 --> 20:52.292
SHE'S BEEN EXHAUSTED,
FORGETFUL, STRESSED --

20:52.292 --> 20:54.043
RUNNING AROUND,
TAKING CARE OF THE KIDS --

20:54.043 --> 20:55.174
I DON'T KNOW.
MAYBE SHE SNAPPED.

20:55.174 --> 20:57.006
WELL, RUNNING AROUND
TAKING CARE OF HER KIDS

20:57.006 --> 20:59.299
DOESN'T SOUND LIKE A MOM
WHO'S ABOUT TO KILL HERSELF,

20:59.299 --> 21:00.840
IN MY EXPERIENCE.

21:00.840 --> 21:01.681
HMM.

21:01.681 --> 21:02.932
IT DOESN'T MAKE SENSE.

21:02.932 --> 21:04.844
HER BLOOD-SUGAR LEVELS
WERE SO LOW WHEN SHE CAME IN.

21:04.844 --> 21:06.306
MY MOTHER
ALWAYS USED TO SAY,

21:06.306 --> 21:08.388
"THE PANCREAS IS
THE SELF-DESTRUCT BUTTON

21:08.388 --> 21:09.559
OF THE BODY."

21:09.559 --> 21:11.100
AND HER PANCREAS
WAS REALLY FRIABLE.

21:11.100 --> 21:12.982
AND HER HUSBAND SAID
SHE'S BEEN FORGETFUL.

21:15.064 --> 21:17.156
I BET THERE'S A TUMOR
ON THAT PANCREAS.

21:17.156 --> 21:18.778
INSULINOMA.

21:18.778 --> 21:21.741
THAT WOULD EXPLAIN HER ANXIETY,
CONFUSION, ERRATIC BEHAVIOR.

21:21.741 --> 21:23.363
THAT WOULD EXPLAIN
EVERYTHING.

21:23.363 --> 21:25.244
YEAH.

21:30.960 --> 21:32.211
I NEED TO CALL
YOUR PARENTS, JACK.

21:32.211 --> 21:33.793
[ SCOFFS ]

21:33.793 --> 21:35.124
[ SIGHS ]

21:35.124 --> 21:36.215
LOOK, YOU'RE SCARED.

21:36.215 --> 21:39.088
YOU THINK
YOU'RE IN TROUBLE NOW.

21:39.088 --> 21:40.009
BUT BELIEVE ME,

21:40.009 --> 21:42.011
THE LONGER YOU WAIT,
THE WORSE IT'LL BE.

21:46.055 --> 21:47.096
LOOK.

21:47.096 --> 21:49.849
YOUR PARENTS ARE SCARED
RIGHT NOW,

21:49.849 --> 21:51.691
WONDERING WHERE YOU ARE.

21:51.691 --> 21:55.274
A-AND THEY'RE GETTING MORE
AND MORE SCARED BY THE MINUTE.

21:55.274 --> 21:58.107
WHEN THEY FINALLY SEE YOU,
THEY'LL BE SO RELIEVED.

22:01.361 --> 22:03.112
BUT...

22:03.112 --> 22:07.156
I MEAN, ALL THAT FEAR
HAS GOT TO GO SOMEWHERE.

22:07.156 --> 22:13.623
ALL THAT FEAR WILL TURN
INTO WHITE-HOT ANGER

22:13.623 --> 22:18.217
THAT WILL BANISH YOU TO A WORLD
WITH NO VIDEO GAMES FOREVER.

22:18.217 --> 22:19.008
[ SIGHS ]
TRUST ME.

22:19.008 --> 22:21.220
I HAVE A LITTLE BOY,
TOO.

22:21.220 --> 22:24.343
I'M A BRICK WALL.

22:25.925 --> 22:27.226
GIVE ME YOUR CELLPHONE.

22:27.226 --> 22:29.098
I'M 7.

22:29.098 --> 22:32.181
WOULD YOU GIVE YOUR 7-YEAR-OLD
A CELLPHONE?

22:32.181 --> 22:34.183
LOOK, I AM TRYING
TO HELP YOU.

22:34.183 --> 22:36.396
IF YOU DON'T COOPERATE,

22:36.396 --> 22:40.440
THEN I'LL HAVE TO CALL
CHILD PROTECTIVE SERVICES.

22:40.440 --> 22:41.571
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT THAT MEANS?

22:44.444 --> 22:45.445
[ SLURPS ]

22:48.658 --> 22:51.200
HEY, YOU WANT TO DO THIS
THE HARD WAY?

22:52.542 --> 22:54.043
THEN I WILL MAKE
THAT CALL.

22:55.495 --> 22:58.668
YOU DO
WHAT YOU'VE GOT TO DO.

23:01.501 --> 23:03.843
I STOLE A CAR ONCE --
WHEN I WAS 12.

23:03.843 --> 23:05.505
DIDN'T MAKE IT
TWO BLOCKS.

23:05.505 --> 23:07.467
[ CHUCKLES ]
WHAT STOPPED YOU?

23:07.467 --> 23:08.768
A DUMPSTER.

23:08.768 --> 23:11.140
MM. FIRST TIME I STOLE A CAR,
I SIDESWIPED THE MIRROR.

23:11.140 --> 23:12.061
FIRST TIME?

23:12.061 --> 23:14.434
SECOND TIME,
I RAN OUT OF GAS.

23:14.434 --> 23:16.476
THIRD,
I GOT AWAY WITH IT.

23:16.476 --> 23:18.017
FOURTH --
FOURTH?

23:18.017 --> 23:19.108
FLAT TIRE.

23:19.108 --> 23:20.780
ARE YOU MESSING WITH ME?
NO.

23:20.780 --> 23:21.901
WAS THERE A FIFTH?

23:21.901 --> 23:23.152
YEAH.
I LIVED IN THAT ONE.

23:23.152 --> 23:24.023
[ CHUCKLES ]

23:24.023 --> 23:25.114
[ ALARM BEEPING ]

23:25.114 --> 23:26.946
DAMN IT.
WHAT JUST HAPPENED?

23:26.946 --> 23:28.988
MESENTERY'S BLEEDING LIKE CRAZY.
WE GOT TO OPEN HIM UP.

23:28.988 --> 23:30.580
I THOUGHT THAT'S WHAT
WE WERE TRYING TO AVOID.

23:30.580 --> 23:33.122
WE GOT NO CHOICE. WE GOT
TO GET IN THERE, AND WE
GOT TO GET IN THERE NOW.

23:33.122 --> 23:34.624
10 BLADE.

23:34.624 --> 23:35.995
10 BLADE!

23:35.995 --> 23:38.538
[ BEEPING CONTINUES ]

23:38.538 --> 23:39.539
ARE YOU ALMOST DONE HERE?

23:39.539 --> 23:40.960
I'VE GOT
TWO TIB-FIB FRACTURES

23:40.960 --> 23:43.042
AND AN L45 COMPRESSION FRACTURE
IN TRAUMA 4.

23:43.042 --> 23:44.043
OKAY. HANG ON.

23:44.043 --> 23:45.505
ALL RIGHT,
I'M GONNA COUNT TO THREE,

23:45.505 --> 23:46.846
AND THEN I'LL DO IT,
OKAY?

23:46.846 --> 23:47.717
OKAY.

23:47.717 --> 23:48.808
YOU READY?
YEAH.

23:48.808 --> 23:50.429
ONE...TWO...

23:50.429 --> 23:53.102
[ CRACK ]
AAH!

23:53.102 --> 23:55.144
AH. ALWAYS BETTER
WHEN YOU DON'T SEE IT COMING.

23:55.144 --> 23:57.016
GO AHEAD AND PUT
A SHOULDER SLING ON HIM, PLEASE.

23:57.016 --> 23:58.608
ALL RIGHT, KEPNER.
WHAT'S NEXT?

23:58.608 --> 24:01.020
I ALREADY TOLD YOU,
IF YOU'D BEEN LISTENING.

24:07.116 --> 24:08.277
WHAT IS GOING ON?

24:08.277 --> 24:09.529
I'M FINE.

24:09.529 --> 24:11.240
NO, YOU'RE NOT,
AND I KNOW

24:11.240 --> 24:14.163
BECAUSE I'M THE QUEEN
OF TAKING MY PERSONAL CRAP
OUT ON OTHER PEOPLE --

24:14.163 --> 24:14.994
ESPECIALLY YOU.

24:14.994 --> 24:16.536
IT LOOKS LIKE THIS.
WHAT'S GOING ON?

24:16.536 --> 24:17.877
I-I DON'T WANT
TO TALK ABOUT IT.

24:17.877 --> 24:19.038
AND I DON'T WANT YOU
SNAPPING AT ME.

24:21.541 --> 24:22.672
YOU CAN'T HAVE A BABY.

24:22.672 --> 24:23.753
EXCUSE ME?

24:23.753 --> 24:25.795
AND IT'S WHAT YOU WANT.

24:25.795 --> 24:28.718
ALL YOU WANT IS TO HAVE A BABY
AND LOVE THAT BABY

24:28.718 --> 24:31.220
AND NURTURE THAT BABY
AND RAISE THAT BABY,

24:31.220 --> 24:33.643
AND THIS WOMAN --
THIS...WOMAN

24:33.643 --> 24:37.727
THROWS HER PERFECTLY HEALTHY
KIDS OFF OF A BRIDGE.

24:37.727 --> 24:40.399
DOESN'T THAT
JUST ENRAGE YOU?

24:40.399 --> 24:41.771
APRIL --
I'M SAYING --

24:41.771 --> 24:45.024
HOW ARE YOU NOT SCREAMING
RIGHT NOW AT WHAT SHE'S DONE?

24:45.024 --> 24:47.567
TO HER KIDS?
TO ALL OF THESE PEOPLE?!

24:47.567 --> 24:49.659
HOW IS
ANY OF THIS FAIR?!

24:49.659 --> 24:51.240
APRIL! APRIL.

24:51.240 --> 24:52.612
April.

24:52.612 --> 24:53.452
OKAY.

24:53.452 --> 24:54.283
NOW --

24:54.283 --> 24:55.494
PATIENTS ARE WAITING.

25:00.169 --> 25:01.460
Greg: UH...

25:01.460 --> 25:05.214
WILL MY DAUGHTER HAVE A SCAR
FOR THE REST OF HER LIFE?

25:05.214 --> 25:06.425
OH.

25:06.425 --> 25:07.967
I TOOK MY TIME.

25:07.967 --> 25:10.509
ANY -- ANY SCAR,
IT WOULD BE VERY MINIMAL.

25:10.509 --> 25:12.181
AH.

25:12.181 --> 25:15.134
EVERY TIME SHE LOOKS IN
A MIRROR, SHE'LL REMEMBER THIS.

25:15.134 --> 25:18.137
MY KIDS...

25:18.137 --> 25:20.560
THEY LOST EVERYTHING.

25:20.560 --> 25:21.641
THEY HAVE YOU.

25:21.641 --> 25:23.482
I DON'T -- I'M NOT SURE
HOW GOOD THAT IS.

25:23.482 --> 25:25.565
LOOK, I MISSED THIS.

25:25.565 --> 25:28.027
YOU KNOW, I...

25:28.027 --> 25:30.570
WHATEVER WAS HAPPENING...

25:30.570 --> 25:31.991
WITH BROOKE...

25:31.991 --> 25:34.113
[ Voice breaking ]
I JUST WASN'T SEEING IT.

25:34.113 --> 25:36.495
YOU KNOW,
YOU WORRY ABOUT EVERYTHING.

25:39.038 --> 25:41.210
BUT I WAS NOT PREPARED
FOR THIS.

25:44.003 --> 25:46.165
SHOULD I HAVE
SEEN IT COMING?

25:46.165 --> 25:51.010
[ Crying ] HOW COULD I
HAVE PREPARED FOR THIS?

25:55.134 --> 25:57.346
WHY DO WE WANT TO AVOID
PUTTING IN ANOTHER PORT?

25:57.346 --> 25:59.178
EACH INCISION
INCREASES THE CHANCES

25:59.178 --> 26:00.680
OF RUPTURING
THE MEMBRANES.

26:00.680 --> 26:01.681
EXACTLY.

26:01.681 --> 26:03.773
[ DOOR OPENS ]

26:03.773 --> 26:05.024
HI. ROBBINS?

26:05.024 --> 26:06.565
UM,
SORRY TO INTERRUPT.

26:06.565 --> 26:09.528
I WANTED TO ASK IF I COULD
MEET WITH YOU AND TALK --

26:09.528 --> 26:11.070
YOU AND ME AND APRIL.

26:11.070 --> 26:13.112
HER HANDS ARE A LITTLE FULL
RIGHT NOW, DOCTOR.

26:14.864 --> 26:16.616
OF COURSE.
WE'RE ALMOST DONE HERE.

26:16.616 --> 26:19.248
YEAH, I MEANT AFTER.
BUT SOON, PLEASE.

26:19.248 --> 26:21.580
I JUST, UM...

26:21.580 --> 26:25.294
I NEED TO BE PREPARED...
FOR WHATEVER IT IS.

26:25.294 --> 26:27.546
WE NEED TO KNOW
EVERYTHING WE CAN.

26:27.546 --> 26:29.508
JUST WHAT IT IS,
WHAT WE CAN DO.

26:29.508 --> 26:31.210
EVERYTHING.

26:31.210 --> 26:32.261
I'LL COME FIND YOU.

26:33.472 --> 26:34.634
ALL RIGHT.

26:37.096 --> 26:38.347
[ SIGHS ]

26:38.347 --> 26:41.100
MY FRIENDS -- THE BABY
WITH OSTEOGENESIS IMPERFECTA.

26:41.100 --> 26:42.521
HMM. I SEE.

26:42.521 --> 26:44.313
YOU'RE CLEAR
ON WHAT TO TELL THEM?

26:44.313 --> 26:45.524
YEAH, I KNOW.

26:45.524 --> 26:48.147
JUST REMEMBER
WHAT I SAID ABOUT HOPE.

26:48.147 --> 26:51.110
DON'T MAKE IT ANY HARDER
FOR THEM THAN IT ALREADY IS.

26:52.361 --> 26:54.573
[ SIGHS ]

26:54.573 --> 26:56.195
CAN YOU TAKE THIS,
PLEASE?

26:56.195 --> 26:56.996
ROBBINS.

26:56.996 --> 26:58.367
I AM DONE HERE.

26:58.367 --> 27:00.199
ROBBINS!

27:03.873 --> 27:05.084
Meredith:
THEY EXAMINED EVERY SLICE?

27:05.084 --> 27:06.706
I STOOD IN PATH
AND WATCHED THEM.

27:06.706 --> 27:07.877
HAVE THEM DO IT AGAIN.

27:07.877 --> 27:09.959
I DID. THERE'S NO EVIDENCE
OF INSULINOMA.

27:09.959 --> 27:11.090
[ SIGHS ]

27:11.090 --> 27:13.132
GET ME THE ULTRASOUND.
THE TUMOR IS IN HERE.

27:13.132 --> 27:14.383
IT DOESN'T HAVE TO BE.

27:14.383 --> 27:16.555
THE HUSBAND SAYS
SHE WAS STRESSED AND OVERTAXED.

27:16.555 --> 27:19.098
SOUNDS LIKE SHE WAS
HEADED FOR A NERVOUS BREAKDOWN.

27:19.098 --> 27:20.890
IT SOUNDS LIKE
SHE'S A MOTHER, OWEN.

27:20.890 --> 27:22.762
WHERE IS
THAT ULTRASOUND?

27:22.762 --> 27:23.893
I'M JUST SAYING,

27:23.893 --> 27:25.434
PEOPLE HAVE BREAKDOWNS
FOR ALL KINDS OF --

27:25.434 --> 27:27.066
OWEN. SHUT UP.

27:33.322 --> 27:35.404
YOU'RE NOT GONNA FIND
ANYTHING.

27:38.117 --> 27:39.328
I'M NOT?

27:41.741 --> 27:42.621
GIVE ME YOUR HAND.

27:47.917 --> 27:48.878
[ GASPS ]

27:48.878 --> 27:50.549
WHAT'S THAT,
RIGHT THERE?

27:50.549 --> 27:52.001
IT'S -- IT'S TINY.

27:52.001 --> 27:53.843
FEELS LIKE
THE HEAD OF A PIN.

27:53.843 --> 27:55.845
RIGHT. BUT IT'S THERE.
I KNEW IT WAS THERE.

27:55.845 --> 27:58.677
EXCELLENT WORK, DR. GREY.

27:58.677 --> 28:00.850
EDWARDS. SCRUB IN.

28:00.850 --> 28:02.181
OKAY.

28:02.181 --> 28:03.803
[ CHUCKLES ]

28:03.803 --> 28:04.854
WHEW!

28:04.854 --> 28:06.225
HMM.

28:10.149 --> 28:11.400
[ SIREN WAILING ]

28:11.400 --> 28:13.522
[ VIDEO GAME MUSIC PLAYING ]

28:13.522 --> 28:15.985
[ BEEP, MUSIC STOPS ]

28:15.985 --> 28:17.076
GIVE ME YOUR PHONE.

28:17.076 --> 28:19.158
I DON'T HAVE A PHONE.

28:19.158 --> 28:20.579
GIVE ME YOUR PHONE!

28:20.579 --> 28:22.081
IT'S NOT MINE.
IT'S DYLAN'S.

28:22.081 --> 28:24.083
THIS IS NOT A GAME,
JACK.

28:24.083 --> 28:26.585
YOUR BROTHER
IS VERY BADLY HURT.

28:26.585 --> 28:29.288
HE IS LYING OPEN
ON AN OPERATING TABLE,

28:29.288 --> 28:32.631
WITH TWO DOCTORS WORKING
VERY HARD TO SAVE HIS LIFE!

28:32.631 --> 28:34.593
THERE ARE
NO RESTART BUTTONS.

28:34.593 --> 28:36.796
THERE'S NO REPLAYS.

28:36.796 --> 28:38.297
THIS IS NOT A GAME.

28:38.297 --> 28:41.390
WHEN IT'S OVER, IT'S OVER.
IT'S REAL.

28:41.390 --> 28:43.803
NOW,
HE NEEDS HIS PARENTS!

28:43.803 --> 28:45.184
SO WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

28:48.227 --> 28:49.939
[ Voice breaking ]
IT'S ALL MY FAULT.

28:49.939 --> 28:52.151
I WANTED TO GO
TO THE ICE-CREAM SHOP,

28:52.151 --> 28:54.153
AND I ASKED HIM
TO DRIVE ME THERE.

28:54.153 --> 28:56.155
I WANT TO GO HOME.

28:56.155 --> 28:58.487
I WANT MY MOM.

29:00.449 --> 29:01.490
[ SNIFFLES ]

29:07.496 --> 29:10.039
Meredith:
SHE SHOULD WAKE UP SOON.

29:10.039 --> 29:11.040
A TUMOR?

29:11.040 --> 29:13.372
BENIGN,
BUT IT SECRETES INSULIN,

29:13.372 --> 29:15.835
WHICH CAUSES MAJOR FLUCTUATIONS
IN GLUCOSE LEVELS.

29:15.835 --> 29:17.216
AND THAT WAS --

29:17.216 --> 29:20.049
THE EXHAUSTION, THE CONFUSION,
THE FORGETFULNESS...

29:20.049 --> 29:21.220
THE ACCIDENT.

29:21.220 --> 29:22.431
IT WAS THE TUMOR.

29:22.431 --> 29:24.183
AND IT'S GONE NOW.

29:24.183 --> 29:25.724
[ SIGHS ]

29:30.269 --> 29:31.480
I'M SORRY.

29:31.480 --> 29:33.392
I SHOULD HAVE NEVER
THOUGHT IT.

29:33.392 --> 29:35.564
NOT FOR ONE SECOND.

29:35.564 --> 29:38.487
I SHOULD HAVE NEVER THOUGHT
THAT YOU WOULD HURT THEM.

29:38.487 --> 29:41.070
I'M SORRY.

29:41.070 --> 29:43.162
IT'S ONLY 4:00 A.M. THERE.

29:43.162 --> 29:45.404
I TOLD CRISTINA TO GO,
TOO.

29:47.616 --> 29:50.409
IT WAS
THE ONLY THING TO DO.

29:50.409 --> 29:52.001
SHE HAD TO GO.

29:52.001 --> 29:54.914
IF SHE'D STAYED,
IT WOULD HAVE BEEN WORSE.

29:54.914 --> 29:56.916
I KNOW THAT NOW.

29:59.718 --> 30:00.679
[ SIGHS ]

30:00.679 --> 30:02.131
TELL HER "HELLO" FOR ME.

30:08.187 --> 30:10.309
ROBBINS, YOU DON'T EVER
WALK OUT OF AN O.R.

30:10.309 --> 30:11.981
IN THE MIDDLE
OF A PROCEDURE -- EVER.

30:11.981 --> 30:14.193
YOU HAVE A SHOT!
YOU HAVE A CHANCE!

30:14.193 --> 30:16.605
AND IT MAY BE SMALL
AND IT MAY BE RISKY,
BUT IT'S A CHANCE.

30:16.605 --> 30:18.697
A CHANCE THAT MY FRIENDS
WOULD GIVE ANYTHING TO HAVE,

30:18.697 --> 30:20.779
AND YOU'RE IGNORING IT --
YOU'RE WASTING IT.

30:29.208 --> 30:30.209
[ DOOR LOCKS ]

30:35.374 --> 30:37.086
[ SIGHS ]

30:41.010 --> 30:42.511
[ SOBS ]

30:44.884 --> 30:46.015
[ CRYING ]

30:50.930 --> 30:52.101
[ SIGHS ]

30:52.101 --> 30:53.933
[ SNIFFLES ]

31:08.407 --> 31:10.249
[ DOOR UNLOCKS ]

31:18.417 --> 31:20.339
DR. GREY?

31:20.339 --> 31:21.800
I'M STILL HERE.

31:23.382 --> 31:24.713
LYNN -- THE NANNY?

31:24.713 --> 31:26.175
OH! LYNN!

31:26.175 --> 31:27.556
I'M SORRY.

31:27.556 --> 31:28.807
YOU'RE STILL HERE?

31:28.807 --> 31:29.388
I AM.

31:29.388 --> 31:31.220
[ GROANS ]

31:33.182 --> 31:34.223
IT'S FINE.

31:34.223 --> 31:36.475
UH, NOW, TELL ME
WHAT IT IS YOU'RE NEEDING.

31:36.475 --> 31:38.317
UH, I, UM...

31:38.317 --> 31:41.020
I NEED, UH, HELP
WITH THE KIDS, OBVIOUSLY.

31:41.020 --> 31:42.731
MORE SPECIFICALLY...?

31:42.731 --> 31:45.114
UH, I NEED...

31:45.114 --> 31:46.445
SUPPORT.

31:46.445 --> 31:50.119
MY LIFE AND MY WORK
IS VERY UNPREDICTABLE.

31:50.119 --> 31:52.331
AND I NEED SOMEONE
WHO UNDERSTANDS THAT

31:52.331 --> 31:55.204
AND WHO CAN BE THERE
WHEN I CAN'T

31:55.204 --> 31:57.586
AND WHO UNDERSTANDS
THAT IF I CAN'T BE THERE,

31:57.586 --> 32:02.041
IT'S BECAUSE
I MUST BE WHERE I AM.

32:02.041 --> 32:04.133
AND I NEED SOMEONE
WHO BELIEVES IN THAT

32:04.133 --> 32:06.095
AND WHO SUPPORTS THAT.

32:09.048 --> 32:11.180
[ SIGHS ]

32:11.180 --> 32:13.682
I NEED A PERSON...

32:13.682 --> 32:17.977
WHO IS IN IT WITH ME...

32:17.977 --> 32:20.149
AND WHO BELIEVES IN THAT.

32:22.061 --> 32:23.732
AND I'M SORRY.
I'M SORRY.

32:23.732 --> 32:25.234
I KNOW...

32:25.234 --> 32:27.156
[ Voice breaking ]
I SEEM LIKE I'M CRAZY.

32:27.156 --> 32:29.488
AND I'M --
I'M REALLY NOT.

32:29.488 --> 32:33.202
BUT...
I'VE JUST HAD THIS DAY.

32:33.202 --> 32:35.414
NO, NO, NO.

32:35.414 --> 32:37.786
[ SIGHS ]

32:37.786 --> 32:39.418
IT'S OKAY.

32:39.418 --> 32:42.841
[ SIGHS ]

32:42.841 --> 32:43.962
[ COMPUTERS BEEPING ]

32:53.262 --> 32:54.933
LET'S TALK.

33:02.981 --> 33:04.983
SEE THIS HERE?
THIS LINEAR HYPOINTENSITY?

33:04.983 --> 33:05.984
IT IS A CSF PLANE.

33:05.984 --> 33:07.866
THAT'S WHAT CAN GIVE ME
A CLEAN DISSECTION.

33:07.866 --> 33:11.030
IF I LEAVE BEHIND
ONE BILLIONTH OF A MALIGNANCY,

33:11.030 --> 33:12.111
THE TUMOR WILL BE BACK,

33:12.111 --> 33:14.453
SO I AM GOING TO HAVE TO USE
EVERY TOOL IN THE BOX --

33:14.453 --> 33:17.116
CUSA, LASERS, FLUOROSCEIN,
RADIOACTIVE SEEDS.

33:17.116 --> 33:20.079
I WILL NOT STOP UNTIL
I HAVE COMPLETELY DECIMATED

33:20.079 --> 33:21.380
EACH AND EVERY LAST CELL.

33:22.751 --> 33:24.043
CHIEF?

33:24.043 --> 33:26.215
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

33:27.546 --> 33:29.218
IT IS...

33:29.218 --> 33:31.050
COMPLEX,
AND IT IS RISKY.

33:31.050 --> 33:32.761
I SEE
THREE SCENARIOS HERE.

33:32.761 --> 33:35.764
ONE, SHEPHERD OPERATES
AND I DIE ON THE TABLE.

33:35.764 --> 33:38.137
TWO, SHEPHERD OPERATES

33:38.137 --> 33:40.439
AND RESECTS
SOMETHING SHE SHOULDN'T

33:40.439 --> 33:42.020
AND I WAKE UP GORKED.

33:42.020 --> 33:44.693
AND THREE --
LEAST LIKELY OF ALL --

33:44.693 --> 33:48.147
SHEPHERD OPERATES,
REMOVES ALL OF THE TUMOR,

33:48.147 --> 33:50.819
AND I WAKE UP ALIVE,
DEFICIT-FREE.

33:50.819 --> 33:51.860
AM I RIGHT?

33:53.912 --> 33:55.204
YES.

33:55.204 --> 33:56.245
BUT AS I --

33:56.245 --> 33:58.457
HOW FAR DOES
THE TUMOR NEED TO REACH

33:58.457 --> 34:01.620
BEFORE IT BECOMES IMPOSSIBLE
TO RESECT IN ITS ENTIRETY?

34:03.001 --> 34:04.423
NICOLE...

34:04.423 --> 34:06.165
WE NEED TO DO THIS NOW.

34:06.165 --> 34:07.716
HOW FAR?

34:10.219 --> 34:11.049
[ SIGHS ]

34:11.049 --> 34:12.931
ONCE IT GOES THROUGH
THE OPTIC APPARATUS

34:12.931 --> 34:14.133
AND BREACHES
THE HYPOTHALAMUS,

34:14.133 --> 34:15.514
THERE'S NO WAY --
I WON'T TOUCH IT.

34:15.514 --> 34:18.347
IF -- IF YOU CLOT
OR BLEED --

34:18.347 --> 34:19.518
IT'S TOO RISKY.

34:21.310 --> 34:22.731
GREAT.
THEN, WE WAIT.

34:22.731 --> 34:25.484
AND WHEN THE TUMOR STARTS
THREATENING THE OPTIC NERVE

34:25.484 --> 34:29.067
AND HEADING TO THE HYPOTHALAMUS,
YOU CAN OPERATE.

34:29.067 --> 34:30.819
THAT IS
A DANGEROUS PLAN.

34:30.819 --> 34:32.691
IT'S A STUPID PLAN.
THIS IS THE PLAN.

34:32.691 --> 34:36.535
YOU GET AT MY TUMOR,
YOU GET AT MY KNOWLEDGE,

34:36.535 --> 34:38.697
I GET AT MY LIFE.

34:38.697 --> 34:40.959
EVERYONE'S HAPPY.

34:52.211 --> 34:53.712
WHEN DID THE PARENTS
GET HERE?

34:53.712 --> 34:55.214
A FEW MINUTES AGO.

34:55.214 --> 34:57.556
I'M WAITING TO SEE IF
THEY HUG THAT KID OR SLAP HIM.

34:57.556 --> 34:58.597
[ CHUCKLES ]

34:58.597 --> 35:00.519
YOU'RE A REALLY GOOD MOM.

35:00.519 --> 35:02.271
WHAT MAKES YOU SAY THAT?

35:02.271 --> 35:04.353
I MEAN, YOU'VE BEEN RIDING ME
ALL DAY,

35:04.353 --> 35:05.984
MAKING SURE
I DON'T SCREW UP.

35:05.984 --> 35:08.687
CRAP, YOU'VE BEEN DOING IT
FOR YEARS.

35:08.687 --> 35:11.280
IT SUCKS, IT'S ANNOYING,
BUT...

35:11.280 --> 35:12.191
IT'S NICE.

35:12.191 --> 35:14.783
[ SCOFFS ]

35:14.783 --> 35:17.446
TUCK STOLE A CANDY BAR
A COUPLE OF WEEKS AGO.

35:17.446 --> 35:19.908
I ONLY FOUND OUT ABOUT IT
LAST NIGHT.

35:19.908 --> 35:23.202
I GOT SO MAD.
I YELLED AT HIM.

35:23.202 --> 35:24.373
TURNS OUT,
BEN ALREADY MADE HIM

35:24.373 --> 35:26.245
GO BACK TO THE STORE
AND PAY FOR THE DAMN THING.

35:26.245 --> 35:27.546
I DIDN'T EVEN KNOW
ABOUT IT.

35:31.510 --> 35:35.013
I MEAN, I'M SO BUSY AT WORK,
I HAVEN'T BEEN THERE TO --

35:37.015 --> 35:39.968
HOW DO I WATCH OUT FOR MY OWN
KID IF I'M NOT EVEN THERE?

35:39.968 --> 35:41.099
HUH?
HOW DO I DO THAT?

35:43.262 --> 35:45.143
I STOLE A BUNCH OF STUFF.

35:45.143 --> 35:46.525
I TURNED OUT OKAY.

35:51.109 --> 35:54.112
TAKE HER UP TO THE I.C.U.
AND CHECK HER COAGS EVERY HOUR.

35:54.112 --> 35:54.983
Nurse: YES, DOCTOR.

35:54.983 --> 35:56.074
[ SIGHS ]

35:56.074 --> 35:57.276
WHO'S NEXT?

35:57.276 --> 35:58.277
THAT'S IT.

35:58.277 --> 36:00.579
TAKE A LOOK
AT THE BOARD, BABE.

36:00.579 --> 36:03.582
EVERYONE'S BEEN
EITHER ADMITTED OR DISCHARGED.

36:04.623 --> 36:08.046
NO, THERE WERE -- THERE WERE
AT LEAST 25 PATIENTS HERE.

36:08.046 --> 36:10.789
AND YOU TREATED
EVERY ONE.

36:10.789 --> 36:13.462
IT'S DAMN GOOD
YOU WERE DOWN HERE.

36:16.675 --> 36:18.637
LISTEN, UM...

36:21.059 --> 36:24.803
YOU AND I HAVE
A REAL CHANCE HERE, YOU KNOW?

36:24.803 --> 36:27.436
WE'RE ABLE
TO SEE THIS THING COMING.

36:27.436 --> 36:30.569
THEN WE ARE GONNA FIND OUT
EXACTLY WHAT IT IS

36:30.569 --> 36:32.020
AND PREPARE OURSELVES.

36:32.020 --> 36:34.313
I ALREADY TALKED TO ARIZONA.
SHE'S GONNA SIT DOWN WITH US.

36:34.313 --> 36:35.574
WE'RE GONNA GET
SOME ANSWERS.

36:35.574 --> 36:37.866
I ALREADY HAVE ANSWERS.

36:37.866 --> 36:40.449
JACKSON, I SPENT ALL NIGHT
LOOKING IT UP.

36:40.449 --> 36:42.701
I PULLED
CASE STUDY AFTER CASE STUDY.

36:42.701 --> 36:44.873
YEAH, I DID THE SAME THING,
BUT THOSE ARE OTHER CASES.

36:44.873 --> 36:47.205
THERE ARE FOUR TYPES
OF OSTEOGENESIS IMPERFECTA,

36:47.205 --> 36:50.208
RANGING FROM A MANAGEABLE
DISABILITY TO COMPLETELY FATAL.

36:50.208 --> 36:52.421
TYPES II AND III
ARE THE MOST SEVERE.

36:52.421 --> 36:54.132
I'M TALKING
ABOUT OUR BABY.

36:54.132 --> 36:55.173
SO AM I.

36:55.173 --> 36:58.337
I STUDIED MY ULTRASOUNDS.

36:58.337 --> 37:01.340
BEST CASE --

37:01.340 --> 37:03.762
OUR KID GETS
SURGERY AFTER SURGERY.

37:03.762 --> 37:08.397
WORST CASE -- OUR KID LIVES
ONLY MINUTES AFTER BIRTH.

37:08.397 --> 37:09.978
MM-HMM.

37:11.810 --> 37:14.403
I DON'T --
I DON'T NEED ANSWERS.

37:14.403 --> 37:17.736
WHAT I NEEDED TODAY
WAS JUST...

37:17.736 --> 37:20.068
TO DO SOMETHING,

37:20.068 --> 37:24.743
TO TREAT THINGS I COULD TREAT,
TO HELP PEOPLE I COULD HELP.

37:24.743 --> 37:25.864
[ SIGHS ]

37:25.864 --> 37:27.666
AT THE VERY LEAST,
UNDO SOME OF THE DAMAGE

37:27.666 --> 37:29.127
THIS LUNATIC WOMAN
DID TO HER KIDS

37:29.127 --> 37:30.669
AND ALL OF THESE PEOPLE
HERE.

37:30.669 --> 37:31.670
SHE HAD A TUMOR.

37:31.670 --> 37:34.172
IT TURNS OUT
SHE HAD AN INSULINOMA.

37:34.172 --> 37:38.046
CAUSES COGNITIVE DEFICITS.
HUNT TOLD ME ALL ABOUT IT.

37:38.046 --> 37:40.969
LOOK, SHE WAS NOT
TRYING TO HURT ANYONE.

37:40.969 --> 37:42.220
SHE HAD...

37:44.803 --> 37:46.385
...NO CONTROL.

37:50.599 --> 37:52.230
[ SIGHS ]

38:01.029 --> 38:02.070
WHY?

38:02.070 --> 38:03.322
[ THUNDER RUMBLES ]

38:03.322 --> 38:04.533
WHY WOULD THAT HAPPEN?

38:04.533 --> 38:07.746
WHY WOULD GOD GIVE HER KIDS,
GIVE HER A FAMILY,

38:07.746 --> 38:09.037
AND LET THAT --

38:09.037 --> 38:11.460
WHY WOULD GOD
LET THAT HAPPEN?!

38:11.460 --> 38:13.291
I-I DON'T UNDERSTAND IT!

38:13.291 --> 38:17.085
YOU CAN DO EVERYTHING RIGHT,
AND I-IT DOESN'T EVEN --

38:20.048 --> 38:21.590
[ SIGHS ] WHY?

38:24.973 --> 38:26.054
I DON'T KNOW.

38:26.054 --> 38:28.226
[ SIGHS ]

38:28.226 --> 38:31.229
I DON'T KNOW.

38:32.431 --> 38:34.433
I -- I JUST --
I DON'T WANT YOU TO HOLD ME,

38:34.433 --> 38:36.355
'CAUSE IF YOU HOLD ME,
I'LL START TO CRY,

38:36.355 --> 38:38.897
AND I DON'T WANT
TO START CRYING.

38:38.897 --> 38:41.199
'CAUSE IF I START CRYING,
I...

38:41.199 --> 38:43.071
I WILL NOT
BE ABLE TO STOP.

38:43.071 --> 38:45.113
I WILL NEVER
BE ABLE TO STOP.

38:46.034 --> 38:47.075
OKAY.

38:47.996 --> 38:50.328
OKAY.

38:50.328 --> 38:52.080
OKAY.

38:54.212 --> 38:55.454
WHATEVER YOU NEED...

38:57.125 --> 38:59.458
...I'M HERE.

39:01.169 --> 39:03.171
[ SOBS ]

39:03.171 --> 39:05.093
[ Voice breaking ]
DID I TELL YOU THAT IT'S A BOY?

39:07.516 --> 39:10.058
[ Crying ]
WE'RE HAVING A BOY.

39:10.058 --> 39:12.601
[ ELLA EYRE'S "IF I GO" PLAYS ]

39:12.601 --> 39:14.352
WHEN SHOCK WEARS OFF...

39:14.352 --> 39:17.025
[ CRYING ]

39:17.025 --> 39:21.189
...WHEN THE BODY CAN ACCEPT
THAT A TRAUMA HAS HAPPENED...

39:23.151 --> 39:25.824
 I COULD PLAY ANY GAME
FOR YOU 

39:25.824 --> 39:27.986
...WHEN IT CAN
LET DOWN ITS DEFENSES...

39:27.986 --> 39:29.488
 ...WHAT YOU WANT ME TO 

39:29.488 --> 39:32.080
 I COULD LIE 

39:32.080 --> 39:33.492
[ Ringing ]

39:33.492 --> 39:34.993
ARE YOU THERE?

39:34.993 --> 39:38.296
UH, NO.
I'M ABOUT TO, UM...

39:38.296 --> 39:39.377
MEREDITH?

39:39.377 --> 39:43.301
I DON'T WANT
TO FIGHT ANYMORE.

39:43.301 --> 39:45.594
[ Sighing ]
OH, I DON'T, EITHER.

39:45.594 --> 39:47.305
And I don't
want you gone.

39:47.305 --> 39:50.969
I KNOW THAT I TOLD YOU
TO GO, BUT...

39:50.969 --> 39:53.772
I MEAN...
THIS ISN'T US.

39:53.772 --> 39:55.854
THIS ISN'T HOW WE END,
IS IT?

39:56.975 --> 39:58.567
I DON'T WANT IT TO.

39:58.567 --> 39:59.778
I'M TRYING.

39:59.778 --> 40:02.320
I'M TRYING, TOO.

40:02.320 --> 40:05.824
LISTEN, MY FLIGHT'S
BEEN DELAYED ALL DAY.

40:05.824 --> 40:07.826
I'M STILL AT THE AIRPORT.
I CAN COME HOME.

40:07.826 --> 40:10.198
...IT'S A SCARY MOMENT.

40:11.910 --> 40:13.452
DO I COME HOME?

40:15.033 --> 40:16.995
WHAT DO WE WANT
TO PROMISE EACH OTHER?

40:16.995 --> 40:21.209
THAT YOU'LL LOVE ME,
EVEN WHEN YOU HATE ME.

40:21.209 --> 40:25.003
"TO LOVE EACH OTHER,
EVEN WE HATE EACH OTHER."

40:25.003 --> 40:26.595
IT'S VULNERABLE.

40:26.595 --> 40:28.717
NO. NO, GO.

40:28.717 --> 40:29.888
MEREDITH.

40:29.888 --> 40:32.390
You know, in -- in --
in a good way. Go.

40:32.390 --> 40:34.012
AND DO
WHAT YOU HAVE TO DO.

40:34.012 --> 40:36.224
WE CAN DO THIS.
PEOPLE DO THIS.

40:36.224 --> 40:39.728
NO RUNNING -- EVER.

40:39.728 --> 40:41.690
NOBODY WALKS OUT,
NO MATTER WHAT HAPPENS.

40:41.690 --> 40:43.441
PEOPLE DO, YES.

40:43.441 --> 40:44.362
Okay.

40:44.362 --> 40:46.525
SO, GO AND DO
WHAT YOU HAVE TO DO.

40:46.525 --> 40:48.326
AND WE WILL
FIGURE THIS OUT.

40:48.326 --> 40:50.118
WE CAN DO THIS.

40:50.118 --> 40:52.621
WE CAN DO THIS.

40:52.621 --> 40:54.122
OKAY.

40:54.122 --> 40:55.834
Okay.

40:55.834 --> 40:58.837
CALL ME WHEN YOU LAND.

40:58.837 --> 41:00.709
And, Derek?

41:00.709 --> 41:01.840
YES?

41:01.840 --> 41:03.131
I'm going to miss you.

41:05.173 --> 41:08.136
THIS CAN WORK.
WE WILL MAKE THIS WORK.

41:08.136 --> 41:09.177
WE WILL.

41:09.177 --> 41:11.259
[ Static ]
ARE YOU STILL THERE?

41:11.259 --> 41:13.141
MEREDITH?

41:14.392 --> 41:15.724
MER --
[ GROANS ]

41:15.724 --> 41:17.265
MEREDITH?
MEREDITH, I'M LOSING YOU.

41:17.265 --> 41:19.598
DEREK?

41:19.598 --> 41:21.810
[ BEEP ]

41:21.810 --> 41:23.191
 ...WILL IT END? 

41:23.191 --> 41:26.194
 WILL YOU LEAVE ME AGAIN? 

41:26.194 --> 41:27.986
 IF I GO 

41:27.986 --> 41:32.701
THIS...IS...FOREVER.

41:37.245 --> 41:38.376
SIGN.

41:48.506 --> 41:50.008
 BUT IF I GO 

41:50.008 --> 41:52.300
NOW WHAT?

41:52.300 --> 41:53.802
NOW I KISS THE BRIDE.

41:53.802 --> 41:55.183
 ...UNTIL I CAN? 

41:55.183 --> 41:58.597
 DO YOU KNOW,
WILL YOU WANT ME? 

41:58.597 --> 42:01.519
 WILL YOU WANT ME LIKE THAT? 

42:01.519 --> 42:05.103
 AND IF I LEAVE, WILL IT END? 

42:05.103 --> 42:07.195
 WILL YOU LEAVE ME AGAIN? 

42:07.195 --> 42:08.947
THE SHOCK RESPONSE
HAD PROTECTED US...

42:08.947 --> 42:12.240
 IF I GO, WILL YOU LOVE ME? 

42:12.240 --> 42:15.243
...AND IT JUST
MIGHT HAVE SAVED US.
